    • Method Detail

      • implement

        public void implement(Class<?> token,
                      Path root)
               throws ImplerException
        Produces code implementing interface specified by provided token.

        Generated class full name is the same as full name of the type token with Impl suffix added. Generated source code is placed in the subdirectory of the specified root directory corresponding to interface's package and has the correct filename. For example, the implementation of the interface List goes to $root/java/util/ListImpl.java

        Specified by:
        implement in interface Impler
        Parameters:
        token - type token to create implementation for
        root - root directory
        Throws:
        ImplerException - when implementation cannot be generated

      • main

        public static void main(String[] args)
        Takes 2 or 3 arguments and either creates an implementation of a specified class or a .jar file containing this implementation. For 2 arguments, the first argument should be a class token and the second one is a root directory. For 3 arguments, the first one should be "-jar", second one is a class token and third one is a path to the desired .jar file.
        Parameters:
        args - an array of String with arguments
